<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The specific name indicates the similarity of this species to its possible sister taxon, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia galii" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia galii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which also feeds on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Galium" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Galium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
